
[1]deliverance

   DELIVERANCE, n.

   1. Release from captivity, slavery, oppression, or any restraint.

   He hath sent me to heal the broken-hearted, to preach deliverance to
   the captives. Luke 4.

   2. Rescue from danger or any evil.

   God sent me to save your lives by a great deliverance. Gen. 45:7.

   3. The act of bringing forth children.

   4. The act of giving or transferring from one to another.

   5. The act of speaking or pronouncing; utterance. [In the three last
   senses, delivery is now used.]

   6. Acquittal of a prisoner, by the verdict of a jury. God send you a
   good deliverance.
